comment: The FHD+ mode doesn’t look as good as a true native FHD display in my opinion. It looks like a 1080p image stretched, so the image looks softer and the aliasing is more apparent. It’s passable in game, but the UI when navigating Windows doesn’t look good.  Considering how excellent the display looks in 4k, I would bet most people will set it there and rarely use the FHD+ option. Sorry I missed that in the video!

I have the same model, and so far I'm mostly happy with it. I still have a bit of doubt - should I have gone for the 18, or should I have gotten a Scar 16 or 18 - but after 2 weeks of umming and ahhing I'm past the return period now! My biggest issues are the price (WHAT was I thinking.....) and lack of ethernet port. There's no excuse for leaving that out IMO. I'm coming from a 2021 Asus Zephyrus G15 and the ethernet port was extremely handy in many work situations. Having to use a dongle is not the end of the world, but for the price and the size of this machine, it should have one. I put a dbrand skin on it, which I'm liking a lot. I've just ordered a couple pf 2TB SSDs so I'll be upgrading  the storage shortly.

I´ve owned two Razer Blade laptops before, namely, the 2019 13-inch (GTX) and the 15-inch advanced 2021 and I can wholeheartedly say that I have never had a more frustrating, money-wasting experience than purchasing a Razer laptop.  They are a perfect example of how expensive laptops do not equal quality, longevity, or a worthwhile experience. They run hot and the batteries bloat, regardless, of how well you take care of the laptops. The Synapse software is incredibly buggy and I can't recommend enough for people to stay away from Razer laptops. DO NOT GET FOOLED BY THE BEAUTIFUL EXTERIOR; THEY ARE ROTTEN TO THE CORE!
